You are so right ! This is how EQ was MEANT to be. I remember back in 98 there was a brief nano-second when ALL servers were RP. At first, everyone made a brief if feeble stab at it, til they were inevitably overwhelmed one by one with L33t D00ds. The feeling of community, outside of one's own guild, was simply not there. It is here. Do you really miss having to turn off /ooc &amp; /auc just to wade your way through east Commons ? I don't. It's called everQUEST, and here people actually do ! It's not 10,000 nameless twinked lvl 60's LFG in Velkators looking for that last bit of AA xp. We dont have the rampant scammers here either, reputation counts for something and that is a good thing. Especially in the 40+ where the population is so small. A wizard isn't doomed to logging on LFG for 10+ hours because he/she isn't the 'ideal' fit for a group, people are more adventurous for the most part. TLC ? Gee, so you might have to actually form friendships with lower levels or hire out mercenaries to help with your quest, once again, a community builder. Yes a lot of the rules make it more CHALLENGING, personally, I was getting burnt on the high end game ( hurry up and wait ) and have found a wonderful refuge here. So FV isn't for everyone. Boo Hoo. Don't let the zone door hit ya where Tunare split ya. <br>
