- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukholdorfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kholdor FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 5:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> There is absolutely NO DATA to support any conclusion that the server is losing it's population.  Just because a handful of people you know leave, means jack all.  With the population indicator being only relative you cannot draw any conclusions.   <br>
<br>
FV has not moved a bit relative to the other server rankings from my perspective...maybe yours is different.  Each time I have logged on it's either the lowest populated, or 2nd lowest with SZ being lowest.  This hasn't changed since day 1 afaik (I started in November, so I don't know for certain if it was higher in October...just my recollection since my old server was in the bottom 10).<br>
<br>
The 'newbie' zones seem relatively populated to me, and has not changed since I started.  Most 30+ zones are pretty empty and have always been (save a few like SK), because most people don't even get to 30+...that is a consistent fact for all servers.   The problem is basically this server has had a low population from day 1.  Has it gotten significantly lower?  I have no idea and nor does anyone else besides VI.<br>
<br>
-kholdOr<br>
